t and fibers as of  the company has  manufacturing sites in  countries crossing four continents asia europe north america and africa and is listed on the stock exchange of thailand set contents  background of the business  beginning of business in thailand  entry into the pet business  entry into the fibers business  background integration into feedstock  becoming global leader  expansion of pet business in us and europe  expansion of polyester business  backward integration into meg  business differentation  high value added hva segments  recycling business  raising capital  initial public offering  rights offering  tender offer  market position  list of subsidiaries  board of directors  shareholding  listing  awardshonorsrecognitions  charitycsr activities  references background of the businessedit beginning of business in thailandedit entry into the pet businessedit indorama ventures commenced business operations in  with the incorporation of indorama holdings ltd which was the first worsted wool yarn producer in thailand the group’s pet business segment comprises primarily the manufacture and sale of pet a plastic polymer resin primarily used for beverage containers and food packaging as well as for the packaging of pharmaceuticals and household products as well as in industrial packaging applications moreover the group also manufactures high value added hva products such as packaging for oxygensensitive foods and beverages in  ivl entered the petrochemical industry focusing on the polyester value chain business with the establishment of a pet resin facility in thailand since then each successive growth and addition has been committed to the polyester value chain it has become a major global polyester value chain producer with a presence in three key business segments pet resin polyester fibers and feedstock comprising pta meg and various eo derivatives the pet business has been achieved through greenfield investments strategic acquisitions and brownfield expansions from  to  pet business has grown after engaging in the downstream production of pet preforms bottles and closures through a joint venture with serm suk pcl as well as through various expansion projects leading to increased capacities entry into the fibers businessedit the group’s fiber business segment comprises the manufacture and sale of a variety of polyester and other types of fibers and yarns which are also used in the group’s hva products particularly in personal care automotive and industrial applications polyester is one of the most widely used synthetic fibers in the world and is a versatile material with wideranging textile and industrial applications the development in the polyester business has been achieved through the acquisition of distressed assets and organic growth through debottlenecking and asset optimization ivl entered into the polyester business in  through the acquisition of indo poly a polyester fiber plant in thailand in  the company acquired tuntex thailand the largest polyester fiber producer in thailand both of the polyester facilities were acquired as distressed assets at a discount to their replacement cost and have been successfully turned around in  indo poly transferred all of its assets to and all of its liabilities were assumed by tuntex thailand which was subsequently renamed indorama polyester industries background integration into feedstockedit the groups feedstock business segment comprises the manufacture production and sale of pta meg eo derivatives and byproducts which are raw materials used in the production of the groups polyester products the groups feedstock business segment supports its pet and polyester business segments and forms part of its strategy to vertically integrate its operations becoming global leaderedit expansion of pet business in us and europeedit the pet production footprint internationally expanded into north america in  with the acquisition of the starpet facility and into europe in  with the commencement of orion global pet facility the expansion made us the only pet resin producer with operations in the three largest consuming regions of asia europe and north america the further expansion of manufacturing presence with the acquisition of two pet resin facilities from eastman chemical company in europe in  and a greenfield investment in the pet business with alphapet in north america in  in the first half of  ivl had completed major acquisitions of pet plants in china indonesia mexico poland and united states leading the company to become the world’s largest pet producer and the largest player in europe pet production footprint was expanded to africa by implementing the new solid state polymerization ssp plant in nigeria which started commercial operations in  in  pt polypet karyapersada which is located at cilegon indonesia was acquired as ivls pet production asset in  ivl has expanded its business into the middle east following the acquisition of two pet plants in turkey one in the southern region and one in northern region of turkey in may  the group also acquired a stake in bangkok polyester public company limited a pet producer in thailand which further consolidated pet production in the local market recently ivl acquired pet business of micro polypet private limited micropet and its two subsidiaries sanchit polymers private limited and eternity infrabuild private limited in india expansion of polyester businessedit in the first half of  polyester production footprint expanded internationally into indonesia and usa later in november  there was an acquisition of the pet and polyester fibers recycling businesses of wellman international in europe which consisted of three production facilities in the republic of ireland the netherlands and france in january  ivl acquired  of fibervisions holdings llc a global manufacturer of specialty mono and bicomponent fibers based in duluth georgia usa backward integration into megedit in  ivl took another step upward to feedstock integration by the acquisition of old world industries i ltd and old world transportation ltd in the usa which is the largest single eoeg production facility in the us mono ethylene glycol meg is one of the company’s key feedstocks together with purified terephthalic acid pta in the manufacture of polyethylene terephthalate pet and polyester fibers and yarns both downstream products of ivl recently the acquisition from compañía española de petróleos cepsa which is pta business in canada and ivl also acquired  of indorama ventures olefins holding llc an old ethylene cracker in usa in september  under refurbishment business differentationedit high value added hva segmentsedit ivl has invested laterally into high value added products in pet polyester fibers and yarns polypropylene fibers and yarns nylon fibers and yarns and purified ethylene oxide peo the expansion into hva products has helped mitigate the weakness that the commodity sector has seen over the past two years allowing us to maintain healthy margins the company has made significant headway on the hva front as a market leader and innovator of numerous products ivls specialty range has enhanced the brand value of ivl making the company a total global solutions provider in  hva portfolio represented  of production and  of consolidated core ebitda core ebitda is calculated as book ebitda less inventory gains or losses less extraordinary items if any recycling businessedit in  ivl acquired wellman international in europe at the beginning of  the company extended the knowhow obtained from wellman international and commenced production of the recycled pet and fiber facility in nakhon pathom thailand ivl expected to further leverage on wellman’s bottle to flake technology on a global scale the company have also integrated three production sites in usa and mexico with recycled pet and objective is to continue to increase the use of recycled pet in the operations raising capitaledit initial public offeringedit indorama ventures public company limited became a public company on september   as of december   the company has registered capital of bt  with paidup capital of bt  totaling  ordinary shares at par value of bt  per share the major shareholder of the company is indorama resources limited owned  by canopus international canopus international is owned by mr aloke lohia and his immediate family and mr sri prakash lohia and his immediate family mr aloke lohia and his immediate family hold  with voting rights over  of total votes of canopus international while mr sri prakash lohia and his immediate family hold  with voting rights over  of total votes of canopus international in january  indorama ventures public company limited completed initial public offering of  ordinary shares at an offering price of baht  per ordinary share the total amount raised in cash from initial public offering of shares baht  million simultaneously the minority shareholders of indorama polymers public company limited subsidiary of ivl listed on the stock exchange of thailand were offered under an exchange offer  ordinary shares of indorama ventures public company limited the ordinary shares of indorama ventures public company limited were listed and commenced trading on the stock exchange of thailand the set on february   the ticker symbol is ivl indorama ventures during the course of  became a member of the major indices set  index ftse set large cap index and msci rights offeringedit in november  the board of directors passed a resolution to increase the authorized share capital from baht  to baht  and reserve the increase in authorized share capital of baht  for the exercise of transferable subscription rights tsr the board approved a rights issue of tsrs to existing shareholders at the ratio of one tsr for every nine existing ordinary shares held of ivl the conversion ratio was  one tsr to one ordinary share and the exercise price of the tsr to ordinary shares is baht  per ordinary share on december   at the extraordinary general meeting of shareholders egm the shareholders approved the issue allocation and the terms and conditions of the tsr on february   the subscription of tsrs was completed with  of tsrs being exercised into shares a total of  new shares started trading on the set on march   the total amount raised in cash from this rights issue is baht  million tender offeredit ivls pet business was listed on the set as indorama polymers public company limited irp in  on december   ivl offered to purchase up to  of irp through a tender offer whereby irp shareholders other than ivl and its subsidiaries were offered ivl shares in exchange for irp shares the said tender offer was completed on february   which resulted in ivl holding directly and indirectly through its subsidiary indorama holdings thailand limited around  of the issued and paidup capital of irp irp shares were delisted from the set on february   onwards market positionedit the pet market in north america is consolidated with the top three companies accounting for nearly  of the market with one third of the market each globally indorama ventures is the market leader the largest polyester fiber producer in thailand  a world scale manufacturer of pta a key raw material for the production of polyester list of subsidiariesedit indorama ventures is headquartered in bangkok thailand as of september  it has  operating sites in  countries in four major regions of the world  europe america africa and asia the company’s portfolio consists of what it calls necessities products vital for life and high valueadded hva products operating sites region country ivls subsidiaries europe ireland wellman international fibers germany trevira fibers php fibers fibers uk beverage plastics packaging the netherlands indorama ventures europe bv pta  pet wellman international bottle flakes denmark fibervisions fibers lithuania orion global pet pet poland indorama ventures poland pet france wellman in